<TITLE> HC rules on high-rise fire equipment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 22 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court asked the government Sunday to explain why it would not be ordered to get firefighting apparatus for high-rises. The court of justices A B M Khairul Haque and Mohammed Abdul Hai issued the rule on a writ petition filed by Human Rights and Peace for Bangladesh. The home, finance and disaster management secretaries, and the director general and director of the Fire Service and Civil Defence to reply in six weeks. Three Supreme Court lawyers Asaduzzaman Siddique, Mohammed Sarwar Ahad Chowdhury and Ekhlas Uddin Bhuiyan filed the petition on Mar 15 on behalf of the rights group. Advocate Manzil Morshed said in the hearing the firemen could take no effective measure beyond the 13th floor during the Mar 13 blaze in Bashundhara shopping complex since they had no modern firefighting equipment. b
